The paper deals with the problem of exploring the secrecy capacity of minimum storage cooperative regenerating (MSCR) codes, which involves information theory and cryptography. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
